laboratory_examinations.findings: Small kidneys (right: 3.8 cm; left: 4.1 cm; normal: 5-6 cm) with diffusely increased echogenicity of the renal cortex and diminished cortico-medullary differentiation, consistent with renal dysplasia.
High-resistance arterial flow in both main renal arteries and extremely elevated resistance to blood flow within the renal parenchyma with no blood flow detectable during diastole.
Normal-sized globes with attenuated optic nerves and near-absence of the optic chiasm.
Detected marked proteinuria (6 g protein/24 hours) and a glomerular filtration rate, based on a 24-hour urine collection, of 20 mL/min (normal: 120 mL/min).
